                            <comment id="12553819" author="ryantxu" created="Thu, 20 Dec 2007 23:25:57 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;change indexDir to dataDir&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12553840" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 21 Dec 2007 01:36:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If one wants the file in the index directory they can specify index/filename&lt;br/&gt;
Does that actually work with the current code (I know I wrote it, but I really don&apos;t recall)?&lt;br/&gt;
Perhaps the test schema should be changed to verify.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12553842" author="ryantxu" created="Fri, 21 Dec 2007 01:48:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;commited.  The test creates a file on the fly... (there isn&apos;t an example using FileFloatSource)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12553844" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 21 Dec 2007 02:02:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Ahhh, I had forgotten that the filename is derived from the fieldname.&lt;br/&gt;
So if the field is named x, the file will be named external_x&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should make the prefix configurable, so hopefully one would be able to set it to index/external_&lt;br/&gt;
if they want those files in the index directory.  The issue is that today, replication only takes a snapshot&lt;br/&gt;
of the index directory, so some people will have to use that until it&apos;s fixed.&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
